RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 54. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. (Horses That Have Raced For $30,000 Or Less Will Be Least Preferred). (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Ra il at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HITTIN MY STRIDE was prompted along in the three path, bid outside the leader turning into the stretch, took the lead, and drew clear under a drive. ABIGAIL'S ROAD stalked in the five path into the turn, took aim under a drive entering the lane, and chased home the winner for place. MARQUETTE WARRIOR raced off the pace in the three path, was ridden between foes in the five path around the turn, floated out to the eight path into the stretch, and kept on for show. AFRAID IM NOTCENTS bumped with an inner foe at the start, chased from out in the center into the turn, swung from the six path into the stretch, and finished evenly. DEMOTION set the pace in the two path, shifted to the rail into the turn, was coaxed from inside into the lane, but faded. UNBRIDLED KISSES rated in the two path, swung out to the seven path turning into the lane, then drifted inwards while making no impact. THAROLITE raced in midfield around the three path but evened out down the lane. SHE'S EXTRA broke out at the start, raced in midpack around the two path but flattened in the stretch. DULCE AMANECER YG was behind in the two path early and never threatened. TEXACANA was wellback in the three path and never menaced. RED RIVER HAWK got pinched at the start, tracked in the six path, but was empty entering the stretch.
